Entry.JapaneseText: ……驚きの頭脳だな…… まだ１３だと言うのに
Entry.EnglishText: ... This is one impressive intellect for a 13 year old girl...

Entry.JapaneseText: おまえのその頭脳は、 いつか我が国を支える、 偉大な財産となる
Entry.EnglishText: If you wish, you can use that intelligence of yours for our country to help assert a better future.

Entry.JapaneseText: よく学べ、メルティア。 おまえは私の自慢の娘だ
Entry.EnglishText: Study well, <MEL>tia. You are my pride and joy.

Entry.JapaneseText: わたしは本当の親に いらないと言われて 捨てられた
Entry.EnglishText: My biological parents decided to throw me out to the streets.

Entry.JapaneseText: ずっと、誰かに 必要とされたかった
Entry.EnglishText: But...I really needed someone. I was a child starving for affection.

Entry.JapaneseText: だから、 １３歳のわたしは、 魔科学研究者を志したの
Entry.EnglishText: That's why at the young age of 13 I decided to start my studies in Magitechnology.

Entry.JapaneseText: そして 魔科学兵器を作ったんだ
Entry.EnglishText: And then we created the Mana Cannon.

Entry.JapaneseText: そう、お父様に 喜んでいただくため
Entry.EnglishText: Yes. Anything to make my father happy.

Entry.JapaneseText: そうすれば、 わたしはずっとお父様に 必要とされる
Entry.EnglishText: In that case father would always appreciate me.

Entry.JapaneseText: でも、わたしには、 いつも恐怖があった
Entry.EnglishText: Still, I was scared during all this time.

Entry.JapaneseText: もし、何もできなくなったら、 わたしはまたいらないって 言われるんじゃないかって
Entry.EnglishText: There was nothing I wouldn't do for him so I was at the mercy of his expectations.

Entry.JapaneseText: だから、必死でがんばったの。 お父様に愛される子でいるために
Entry.EnglishText: That's why I was so desperate. I needed to stay as father's pride and joy.

Entry.JapaneseText: 本当に、そう？ そこまでしなくても、 あなたを……
Entry.EnglishText: Is that true? But you've gone as far as to...

Entry.JapaneseText: わたしを 必要としてくれる人は、 他にも……
Entry.EnglishText: I mean... there are important people in my life too, yet...

Entry.JapaneseText: あなたにはわからない！
あなたが妬ましかった。 不必要だと言われることなく、
Entry.EnglishText: I am jealous of you. There's no need for me to say it for you to understand.

Entry.JapaneseText: 常に何者かに 守られているあなたが
Entry.EnglishText: You always had someone to love you and take care of you.
